        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 30 at 3:12AM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 312 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 19 miles northwest of Gillham to near
Horatio, or extending from 26 miles northwest of Umpire to near
Horatio, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
De Queen, Dierks, Horatio, Umpire, Lockesburg, Gillham, Athens,
Geneva, Lebanon, Provo, Burg, West Line, West Otis, Cerrogordo,
Shinewell, Plunketville, Muddy Fork, Watson and America.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
